1. Update the posts table by adding a column that stores the date and time when a post is created.
- Each post must display this timestamp in the interface.

2. Create a new table named comments that stores:
- a unique comment identifier
- the related post identifier
- the user identifier of the commenter
- the comment description
- the date and time the comment was created
- All comments should be displayed below their corresponding post.

3. Define foreign key constraints that connect:
- comments to posts
- comments to accounts

4. Delete post feature
- Add a delete option to every post.
- Ensure that only a logged-in user can perform deletion
- a user can delete only their own posts
- a confirmation or error message is displayed after deletion

5. Update post feature
- Provide a way to edit existing posts.
- Ensure that the owner of the post can edit it

6. Profile page - Create a separate profile page that displays:
- the user’s personal information
- all posts created by that user
- the timestamps of those posts
- Navigation between the dashboard and the profile page should be available.